Identify High and Low Tides¶

In [8]: 
##-- Find min & max from dataset
decluster = 5

# for local maxima
localmax = array( argrelextrema(data.values, np.greater_equal) )
localmax = localmax[0, (localmax[0,1:] - localmax[0,:-1]) > decluster ]

# for local minima
localmin = array( argrelextrema(data.values, np.less_equal) )
localmin = localmin[0,  (localmin[0,1:] - localmin[0,:-1]) > decluster ]

# Plot tides with high and low marked in red
fh = pyplot.figure(figsize=(20, 6), dpi=120)
data.plot(color='blue')
data.ix[localmax].plot(color='red', marker='.')
data.ix[localmin].plot(color='red', marker='.')

Divide HHW/HW and LLW/LW¶

In [9]: 
##-- Find higher high water and lower low water

# Collect high and low values.  Clear ends, since they're skewed by the boundary.
high = data.ix[localmax][1:-1]
low = data.ix[localmin][1:-1]

# Calculate Higher High and High tides
mask = zeros(shape(high))
for i in xrange(len(high) - 1):
   if high[i] >= high[i+1]: mask[i] = 1
if high[-1] > high[-2]: mask[-1] = 1

# Check for skipped higher high's
for i in xrange(2,len(mask)-2):
    if sum(mask[i-1:i+3])<0.5: mask[i]=1
    
hw = high[mask==0]
hhw = high[mask==1]

# Calculate Lower Low and Low tides
mask = zeros(shape(low))
for i in xrange(len(low) - 1):
   if (low[i] <= low[i+1]): mask[i] = 1
if low[-1] < low[-2]: mask[-1] = 1
    
# Check for skipped lower lows
for i in arange(1,len(mask)-1,1):
    if sum(mask[i-1:i+2])<0.5: mask[i]=1
    if sum(mask[i-1:i+2])>2.5: mask[i]=0
    
###print(mask)
lw = low[mask==0]
llw = low[mask==1]

# Plot time series
fh = pyplot.figure(figsize=(20, 6), dpi=120)
data.plot(color='blue')
hw.plot(color='red', marker='.')#, ls='None')
hhw.plot(color='green', marker='.')#, ls='None')
lw.plot(color='red', marker='.')#, ls='None')
llw.plot(color='green', marker='.')#, ls='None')

Divide Spring and Neap Tides¶

(1) Selecting by peak/trough of HHW/LLW Curve¶

In [11]: 
##--  Locate Spring/Neap points

# for HHW spring/neap points
hhw_max = array( argrelextrema(hhw.values, np.greater_equal), dtype='int')
hhw_min = array( argrelextrema(hhw.values, np.less_equal), dtype='int')
# for LLW spring/neap points
llw_max = array( argrelextrema(llw.values, np.greater_equal), dtype='int')
llw_min = array( argrelextrema(llw.values, np.less_equal), dtype='int')

hhw_max=hhw_max[0,:]
hhw_min=hhw_min[0,:]
llw_max=llw_max[0,:]
llw_min=llw_min[0,:]


##--------------- PLOTTING -----------------------
# plot full dataset
fh = pyplot.figure(figsize=(20, 6), dpi=120)
data.plot(color='blue')

# HHW indecies (highest +/-2)
hhw_max_idx1 = numpy.maximum(hhw_max - 2, zeros(shape(hhw_max), dtype='int'))
hhw_max_idx2 = numpy.minimum(hhw_max + 3, (zeros(shape(hhw_max), dtype='int') + len(hhw)+1))
hhw_min_idx1 = numpy.maximum(hhw_min - 2, zeros(shape(hhw_min), dtype='int'))
hhw_min_idx2 = numpy.minimum(hhw_min + 3, (zeros(shape(hhw_min), dtype='int') + len(hhw)+1))

# LLW indecies (lowest +/-2)
llw_max_idx1 = numpy.maximum(llw_max - 2, zeros(shape(llw_max), dtype='int'))
llw_max_idx2 = numpy.minimum(llw_max + 3, (zeros(shape(llw_max), dtype='int') + len(llw)+1))
llw_min_idx1 = numpy.maximum(llw_min - 2, zeros(shape(llw_min), dtype='int'))
llw_min_idx2 = numpy.minimum(llw_min + 3, (zeros(shape(llw_min), dtype='int') + len(llw)+1))

# Plot Spring HHW
hhw_mx = hhw.ix[hhw_max_idx1[0]:hhw_max_idx2[0]]
for i in xrange(1,len(hhw_max_idx1)):
    hhw_mx = pd.concat([hhw_mx, hhw.ix[hhw_max_idx1[i]:hhw_max_idx2[i]]])
hhw_mx.plot(color='green', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')

# Plot Neap HHW
hhw_mn = hhw.ix[hhw_min_idx1[0]:hhw_min_idx2[0]]
for i in xrange(1,len(hhw_min_idx1)):
    hhw_mn = pd.concat([hhw_mn, hhw.ix[hhw_min_idx1[i]:hhw_min_idx2[i]]])
hhw_mn.plot(color='red', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')

# Plot Neap LLW
llw_mx = llw.ix[llw_max_idx1[0]:llw_max_idx2[0]]
for i in xrange(1,len(hhw_max_idx1)):
    llw_mx = pd.concat([llw_mx, llw.ix[llw_max_idx1[i]:llw_max_idx2[i]]])
llw_mx.plot(color='red', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')

# Plot Spring LLW
llw_mn = llw.ix[llw_min_idx1[0]:llw_min_idx2[0]]
for i in xrange(1,len(llw_min_idx1)):
    llw_mn = pd.concat([llw_mn, llw.ix[llw_min_idx1[i]:llw_min_idx2[i]]])
llw_mn.plot(color='green', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')

mean_sp_np = pd.DataFrame([[mean(hhw_mx), mean(hhw_mn)], [mean(llw_mn),mean(llw_mx)]], columns=['SPRING', 'NEAP'], index=['MHHW', 'MLLW'])
print('Mean Tide Conditions from Method 1\n')
print(mean_sp_np)
print()

(2) Selecting by Rank (highest vs lowest half of HHW & LLW datasets)¶

In [12]: 
##--Find largest & smallest halves of hhw & llw records
##--   This method doesn't robustly identify spring vs neap low tides, since the weaker spring tide never gets very low

hhw_order = hhw.order()
hhw_midIdx = int(len(hhw_order)/2)

llw_order = llw.order()
llw_midIdx = int(len(llw_order)/2)

# Plot time series
fh = pyplot.figure(figsize=(20, 6), dpi=120)
data.plot(color='blue')
hhw_order[hhw_midIdx:].plot(color='green', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')
hhw_order[:hhw_midIdx].plot(color='red', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')
llw_order[:llw_midIdx].plot(color='green', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')
llw_order[llw_midIdx:].plot(color='red', marker='o', ms=8, ls='None')

mean_SpNp_Halves = pd.DataFrame([[mean(hhw_order[hhw_midIdx:]), mean(hhw_order[:hhw_midIdx])], [mean(llw_order[:llw_midIdx]),mean(llw_order[llw_midIdx:])]], columns=['SPRING', 'NEAP'], index=['MHHW', 'MLLW'])
print('Mean Tide Conditions from Method 1\n')
print(mean_SpNp_Halves)
print()
